      "writtenOn": "2026-07-09T18:31:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "[warning] Line 87: None of the branches clamp the derived geometry to an upper bound. For a portrait remote video (videoInvAspect \u003e 1) the width-driven branch computes newHeight \u003d width * videoInvAspect (e.g. 400 * 1.78 ≈ 711), and the area-preserving branch is likewise unbounded above. On small displays this can make the PiP window taller/wider than the screen or push it partially off-screen, with no way to shrink it back below the aspect-derived size. Clamp against Screen.desktopAvailableWidth/Height (or a maximumWidth/maximumHeight) after deriving newWidth/newHeight, re-deriving the opposite dimension when the clamp bites, the same way the minimum-size clamps are handled.",
      "revId": "cf7d8797483a9b0f42b62be2a8ead04d258df0dc",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
    },
