      "message": "[info] Line 62: remoteVideo.invAspectRatio falls back to 0.5625 (16:9) whenever videoOutput.sourceRect is empty (see VideoView.qml:28). Since videoInvAspectRatio gates only on isRendering, the window can be resized to a hard-coded 16:9 the instant rendering flips true but before a real frame has sized sourceRect, then resized again once the true aspect is known — a visible double snap for non-16:9 sources. Consider also requiring sourceRect.width \u003e 0 (or exposing the raw ratio without the default) so the aspect adjustment only fires on a genuine measured aspect.",
